./sdp/logs/Verify_T-009_20260416T043834Z_1776335333.log:220:{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":"2026-04-16T10:30:50.219Z","tool_name":"write_file","tool_id":"write_file_1776335450219_0","parameters":{"content":"# Verification Report — T-009@20260416T043834Z\n\n**Verify Agent:** Gemini CLI\n**Date:** 2026-04-16\n**Artifacts Reviewed:** `my-claw/tools/senseweave/resource_governor.py`, `my-claw/tools/duet_composer.py`, `my-claw/tools/daemon.py`, `my-claw/tools/cypherclaw_daemon.py`, `tests/test_governor_integration.py`, `tests/test_daemon_fallback.py`, `tests/test_generative_scores.py`, `tests/test_audio_analysis.py`, `tests/test_continuous_learner.py`\n\n## Correctness\nThe implementation successfully adds live performance resource governance as specified. `resource_governor.py` correctly samples CPU pressure, SC node count, sampler load, capture freshness, self-listener RMS, and master bus health. These signals are collapsed into a composite pressure score that drives degradation rules. `duet_composer.py` integrates these rules by shedding optional roles (color, counter-melody) and thinning events (grains, non-accent notes) before affecting primary musical density.\n\n## Completeness\nAll acceptance criteria are met. The degradation order (least to most impactful) is implemented as requested. The hardening requirement to invoke `bootstrap_identity()` on startup in both standalone (`cypherclaw_daemon.py`) and federated (`daemon.py`) modes is implemented and verified by AST-based integration tests.\n\n## Consistency\nThe new `resource_governor.py` module is consistent with the project's architecture and follows existing coding patterns. Integration into the composer loop in `duet_composer.py` is surgical and well-aligned with established event-handling logic.\n\n## Security\nNo security vulnerabilities were identified. All signal reads are from local system state files or standard system APIs (`os.getloadavg`). No sensitive information is logged or transmitted.\n\n## Quality\nThe code is high quality, well-documented, and follows established patterns. The test coverage is comprehensive, including unit tests for the governor logic and integration tests that verify budget enforcement and startup wiring. All relevant tests pass (171 tests total in the reviewed suite).\n\n## Issues Found\n- [ ] No blocking or material issues identified.\n\n## Verdict: PASS\n\n## Notes for Lead Agent\n- Great work on the resource governor implementation and the inclusion of the `bootstrap_identity` hardening in the same task.\n- The AST-based tests for startup wiring are a robust way to verify initialization order without requiring complex mocking of full daemon environments.\n","file_path":"sdp/verification/t-009@20260416t043834z-verify.md"}}
